France Aims to Cut Legal Immigrants by 20,000 Per Year, TF1 Says

-- B y   H e a t h e r   S m i t h
-- 
2011-04-16T09:46:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/france-aims-to-cut-legal-immigrants-by-20-000-per-year-tf1-says.html
France  plans to reduce the number
of legal immigrants allowed into the country by 20,000 a year,
Interior Minister Claude Gueant said yesterday in an interview
broadcast on TF1 television.  That would bring the number of legal immigrants down to
180,000 annually from the current level of 200,000, Gueant said,
according to a  report  on the interview on the TV stationâ€™s
